921
01:55:57,597 --> 01:55:58,973
My goodness.

922
01:56:00,058 --> 01:56:04,897
- You don't want to go up?
- Nope. I don't do these kind of things.

923
01:56:08,485 --> 01:56:10,903
I spent most of my life in the Army.

924
01:56:13,740 --> 01:56:18,494
New Year's Eve, 1957,
I was stationed in Okinawa.

925
01:56:19,997 --> 01:56:24,000
My wife and son were here in the States
just driving down the road,

926
01:56:24,084 --> 01:56:27,628
and some fella who'd had too much
to drink plowed right into them.

927
01:56:28,171 --> 01:56:30,172
Killed them both.

928
01:56:34,553 --> 01:56:39,682
Now you might think
the last thing I would do in the world

929
01:56:42,519 --> 01:56:44,312
is go to the whiskey.

930
01:56:46,023 --> 01:56:50,234
But at the time,
it felt like the only thing I could do.

931
01:56:50,319 --> 01:56:52,945
And I did it hard!

932
01:56:55,949 --> 01:56:58,451
But pretty soon I realized

933
01:56:59,202 --> 01:57:03,456
I wasn't doing my wife and son any good
mourning them with the bottle.

934
01:57:03,832 --> 01:57:07,877
So I pulled myself together
and I quit drinking,

935
01:57:08,545 --> 01:57:09,920
cold turkey.

936
01:57:11,214 --> 01:57:15,593
So since all that, this is pretty much me.

937
01:57:16,887 --> 01:57:19,138
Do you ever travel, Mr. Franz?

938
01:57:20,182 --> 01:57:23,267
No, I can't seem to get too far
from my leather.

939
01:57:24,978 --> 01:57:29,565
I do a lot of leather engraving.
I got a little workshop out in the garage.

940
01:57:29,900 --> 01:57:32,109
Between that and my pension,
I do pretty well.

941
01:57:32,194 --> 01:57:34,737
But every time I think
I might take a trip somewhere,

942
01:57:34,821 --> 01:57:38,449
I get too far behind on orders and such
to consider it.

943
01:57:39,326 --> 01:57:41,994
When we finish eating,
I'd love to see your workshop.

944
01:57:42,079 --> 01:57:43,496
- Would you?
- Oh, yeah.

945
01:57:43,580 --> 01:57:45,373
I was hoping you'd say that.

946
01:57:45,457 --> 01:57:48,417
- It's amazing how malleable this is.
- Yeah, it is.

947
01:57:48,502 --> 01:57:50,211
When the leather is wet you can really...

948
01:57:50,295 --> 01:57:51,629
- It's like butter.
- Yeah.

949
01:57:51,713 --> 01:57:55,257
It's amazing. And then it hardens up,
and, I mean, it stays right there.

950
01:58:40,305 --> 01:58:45,977
A good whack with the mallet.
Crack it down. Whack. Bang.

951
01:59:46,330 --> 01:59:49,999
I went to South Dakota.
I worked at a grain elevator

952
01:59:50,083 --> 01:59:52,627
for this guy named Wayne.
He was a really good guy.

953
01:59:52,711 --> 01:59:54,295
So I took the Colorado River

954
01:59:54,379 --> 01:59:57,673
all the way down through
the Grand Canyon and did rapids,

955
01:59:57,758 --> 02:00:01,385
which is by far one of
the scariest things I've ever done.

956
02:00:01,512 --> 02:00:06,891
And I took the Colorado down into
Mexico, Golfo, where I got stuck.

957
02:00:07,768 --> 02:00:10,102
Salvation Mountain. The Slabs.

958
02:00:11,814 --> 02:00:13,940
What's the "N" stand for?

959
02:00:15,567 --> 02:00:16,734
North.

960
02:00:18,028 --> 02:00:19,695
Alaska?

961
02:00:22,699 --> 02:00:25,201
Son, what the hell
are you running from?

962
02:00:26,328 --> 02:00:28,788
You know, I can ask you
the same question!

963
02:00:29,832 --> 02:00:32,250
Except I already know the answer!

964
02:00:33,085 --> 02:00:34,585
You do, do you?

965
02:00:35,337 --> 02:00:39,590
I do, Mr. Franz!
You got to get back out in the world!

966
02:00:40,386 --> 02:00:43,596
Get out of that lonely house,
that little workshop of yours.

967
02:00:43,681 --> 02:00:47,725
Get back out on the road! Really!

968
02:00:48,602 --> 02:00:51,229
You're going to live a long time, Ron!

969
02:00:51,313 --> 02:00:54,607
You should make a radical change
in your lifestyle!

970
02:00:55,276 --> 02:00:59,195
I mean, the core of man's spirit
comes from new experiences.

971
02:00:59,738 --> 02:01:03,950
And there you are, stubborn old man,
sitting on your butt.

972
02:01:05,077 --> 02:01:07,912
- Sitting on my butt?
- Yeah.

973
02:01:09,456 --> 02:01:13,877
I'll show you sitting on my butt!

974
02:01:13,961 --> 02:01:16,004
"Stubborn old man."

975
02:01:17,464 --> 02:01:19,132
I'll show you!

976
02:01:19,633 --> 02:01:21,843
Come on, then! Come on.

977
02:01:24,805 --> 02:01:27,932
Sitting on my butt? Yeah.

978
02:01:30,019 --> 02:01:32,186
Come on, old man. Come climbing.

979
02:01:32,271 --> 02:01:33,980
Sitting on my butt.

980
02:01:34,315 --> 02:01:35,815
Come on. Keep going!

981
02:01:39,653 --> 02:01:41,362
You're doing great!

982
02:01:46,160 --> 02:01:48,828
- Keep going. Keep going, Ron!
- Yeah!

983
02:01:50,581 --> 02:01:54,334
Can anybody see this?
God, are you watching this right now?

984
02:02:02,509 --> 02:02:03,635
Yeah.

985
02:02:06,680 --> 02:02:11,017
- You all right?
- You little pinhead!

986
02:02:28,535 --> 02:02:30,870
I'm gonna miss you when you go.

987
02:02:32,498 --> 02:02:36,167
I'll miss you, too, Ron.
But you're wrong if you think

988
02:02:36,251 --> 02:02:40,213
that the joy of life comes principally
from human relationships.

989
02:02:41,215 --> 02:02:43,549
God's placed it all around us.
It's in everything.

990
02:02:43,634 --> 02:02:46,010
It's in anything we can experience.

991
02:02:46,887 --> 02:02:50,390
People just need to change the way
they look at those things.

992
02:02:50,474 --> 02:02:52,684
Yeah, I'm gonna take stock of that.

993
02:02:54,561 --> 02:02:55,853
No, I am.

994
02:03:00,069 --> 02:03:01,152
I am.

995
02:03:03,531 --> 02:03:05,740
But I wanted to tell you something.

996
02:03:09,495 --> 02:03:12,247
From the bits and pieces I put together,

997
02:03:12,331 --> 02:03:16,418
you know, from what you told me about
your family, your mother and your dad.

998
02:03:18,421 --> 02:03:21,756
And I know you've got your problems
with the church, too.

999
02:03:23,676 --> 02:03:27,429
But there's some kind of bigger thing
we can all appreciate,

1000
02:03:28,431 --> 02:03:31,641
and it sounds like
you don't mind calling it God.

1001
02:03:37,732 --> 02:03:40,650
But when you forgive,

1002
02:03:42,903 --> 02:03:44,154
you love.

1003
02:03:47,908 --> 02:03:50,952
And when you love,

1004
02:03:51,787 --> 02:03:54,372
God's light shines on you.

1005
02:03:59,086 --> 02:04:02,797
- Holy shit.
- I told you about that language.

1006
02:04:12,975 --> 02:04:14,476
I told you so!

1007
02:04:17,354 --> 02:04:20,899
Where are the fucking animals now?
I'm hungry!

1008
02:04:21,025 --> 02:04:25,236
I'm fucking hungry! I'm fucking hungry!

1009
02:04:42,296 --> 02:04:46,049
<i>"For a moment she rediscovered
the purpose of her life.</i>

1010
02:04:46,926 --> 02:04:50,637
<i>"She was here on earth to grasp
the meaning of its wild enchantment,</i>

1011
02:04:50,721 --> 02:04:53,556
<i>"and to call each thing
by its right name."</i>

1012
02:04:56,852 --> 02:04:58,520
"By its right name."

1013
02:04:59,313 --> 02:05:01,648
What is this? What is this one?

1014
02:05:04,693 --> 02:05:09,656
<i>This is Viburnum edule.
Viburnum edule.</i>

1015
02:05:14,495 --> 02:05:17,497
<i>Hedysarum alpinum.</i>

1016
02:05:19,585 --> 02:05:24,297
Hedysarum alpinum is wild potato root.
Wild potato root.

1017
02:05:26,551 --> 02:05:30,220
<i>Epilobium angustifolium. Fireweed.</i>

1018
02:08:25,606 --> 02:08:28,525
Fuck it all. Fuck it all!

1019
