Hi.

1020
02:11:08,062 --> 02:11:11,231
What are you doing up?
It's 3:30 in the morning.

1021
02:11:11,566 --> 02:11:14,776
I heard you get off the couch
about a half hour ago.

1022
02:11:16,070 --> 02:11:19,781
Had a funny feeling
you might not be here for our breakfast.

1023
02:11:23,995 --> 02:11:28,916
I'm gonna drive you 100 miles to
someplace where you can catch a train,

1024
02:11:29,667 --> 02:11:34,379
a plane or hitch a ride
and not get stuck out in this desert.

1025
02:11:35,590 --> 02:11:39,593
I'd take you all the way to Alaska
if I didn't have an 8:00 mass.

1026
02:11:39,928 --> 02:11:43,347
- Ron, you don't have to do that.
- I want to do it.

1027
02:11:44,224 --> 02:11:47,226
Get you started on this thing of yours.

1028
02:11:47,685 --> 02:11:49,728
- On my great...
- I know.

1029
02:11:50,396 --> 02:11:52,940
On your great Alaskan adventure.

1030
02:11:53,733 --> 02:11:56,443
Here. Here's a machete.

1031
02:11:58,780 --> 02:12:03,617
Collapsible fishing pole, a few other
odds and ends I stuck in there for you.

1032
02:12:07,080 --> 02:12:09,498
- Ron...
- Just take it.

1033
02:12:10,875 --> 02:12:13,710
I'll get dressed
and meet you in the truck.

1034
02:13:09,978 --> 02:13:11,604
Well, my friend.

1035
02:13:14,065 --> 02:13:15,149
Yep.

1036
02:13:19,529 --> 02:13:22,031
I had an idea.

1037
02:13:23,158 --> 02:13:27,828
You know, my mother was an only child

1038
02:13:28,705 --> 02:13:30,539
and so was my father,

1039
02:13:31,166 --> 02:13:35,461
and I was their only child,

1040
02:13:38,840 --> 02:13:41,550
so when I'm gone,
I'm the end of the line.

1041
02:13:42,594 --> 02:13:44,720
My family will be finished.

1042
02:13:48,391 --> 02:13:53,729
What do you say you let me adopt you?

1043
02:13:58,068 --> 02:14:02,196
I can be, say, your grandfather.

1044
02:14:06,576 --> 02:14:08,202
Ron,

1045
02:14:09,788 --> 02:14:13,582
could we talk about this
when I get back from Alaska?

1046
02:14:13,958 --> 02:14:15,751
Would that be okay?

1047
02:14:23,051 --> 02:14:26,261
Yeah, yeah. We can do that. Yeah.

1048
02:14:31,226 --> 02:14:32,559
All right, Ron.

1049
02:14:34,938 --> 02:14:36,271
Thank you.

1050
02:15:25,407 --> 02:15:27,616
<i>What did his voice sound like now?</i>

1051
02:15:28,869 --> 02:15:31,078
<i>What would he tell about now?</i>

1052
02:15:31,538 --> 02:15:34,665
...nine, ten.

1053
02:16:24,299 --> 02:16:29,261
<i>I realized that the words to my thoughts
were of less and less meaning.</i>

1054
02:16:29,346 --> 02:16:31,472
<i>Chris was writing his story,</i>

1055
02:16:32,933 --> 02:16:35,935
<i>and it had to be Chris who would tell it.</i>

1056
02:18:56,703 --> 02:18:59,163
<i>"To call each thing by its right name.</i>

1057
02:19:04,044 --> 02:19:05,753
<i>"By its right name."</i>

1058
02:19:56,932 --> 02:19:58,975
<i>What if I were smiling</i>

1059
